question: How do I order medicines on CareLoop?
variations: How can I place a medicine order?
How to buy medicines in the app?
Where do I order my medicines?
answer: You can order medicines through our chat interface. Simply upload your prescription or type the medicine name. Nearby pharmacies will receive the request and the first to accept will prepare and deliver your order.

question: Can I order medicines without a prescription?
variations: Do I need a prescription for all medicines?
Can I buy medicines without prescription?
answer: You can order OTC (over-the-counter) medicines without a prescription. For regulated or Schedule-H drugs, you must upload a valid prescription as per government guidelines.

question: How are pharmacies selected for my order?
variations: How do you choose the pharmacy?
answer: Your request is broadcast instantly to nearby partnered pharmacies. The first store to accept the order gets it and prepares the medicines.

question: Can I track my order in real time?
answer: Yes, you can track your order in real time from the app. Once a helper picks up your medicines, live location tracking becomes active until delivery is completed.

question: What if the pharmacy does not have my medicine?
variations: What if stock is not available?
Pharmacy does not have the item
answer: If the pharmacy cannot fulfill the order, the request automatically goes to the next pharmacy or our AI suggests substitute brands with the same salt composition.

question: Can I chat with pharmacies for clarification?
answer: Yes, you can message the pharmacy directly through the chat window for clarifications about availability, alternatives, or delivery time.

question: How long does medicine delivery usually take?
variations: When will I get my medicines?
answer: Most orders are fulfilled within 15-45 minutes based on pharmacy distance and helper availability, since the entire system is hyperlocal.

question: Can I cancel an order after placing it?
answer: Yes, you can cancel your order before it has been prepared or picked up. After pickup, cancellation may not be possible.

question: Can I reorder previous medicines?
answer: Yes, you can reorder any past medicine with one tap from your order history or through the AI reminder system.

question: Does the app support voice-based ordering?
answer: Yes, you can speak your medicine names or requests. Our AI converts your voice into text and processes your order seamlessly.

question: Can I schedule a medicine delivery for a future date and time?

question: Is same-day return available if I change my mind?

question: How do I request a specific brand (not generic) when ordering?

question: Are medicines sold on CareLoop legally verified?
variations: How do you ensure legal compliance?
Are medicines authentic on this platform?
answer: Yes  every partnered pharmacy must upload valid drug licenses and pass compliance checks. All medicines are sourced and distributed according to official pharmaceutical regulations.

question: Does CareLoop follow prescription regulations?
answer: Yes  Schedule H and prescription-only medicines require an authentic prescription. The platform uses OCR and pharmacist review to enforce compliance strictly.

question: Who verifies the substitute medicines suggested by AI?
answer: Substitutes suggested by AI are validated by licensed pharmacists before dispatch to ensure accuracy, dosage safety, and therapeutic equivalence.

question: Is my medical data stored securely?

question: Do delivery helpers handle medicines safely?
answer: Helpers undergo training on safe handling, storage protection, temperature safety, and privacy guidelines to ensure reliable delivery.

question: How does CareLoop prevent medicine misuse?
variations: How do you stop illegal purchases?

question: Are doctor consultations compliant with telemedicine laws?
answer: Yes  all consultations follow Telemedicine Practice Guidelines. Only verified and licensed doctors conduct video, audio, or text sessions.

answer: Partner labs follow certified hygiene standards. Technicians use sterile and single-use equipment to ensure safe sample collection.

question: Does CareLoop store my payment information?
answer: CareLoop does not store sensitive payment details. All transactions are handled through secure, PCI-DSS-compliant payment gateways.

question: What should I do if I receive a damaged or outdated medicine?
answer: Report the issue from your order details. The pharmacy will verify the claim and process a replacement or refund according to compliance rules.

question: How do you verify pharmaceutical invoices to prevent counterfeit products?
answer: We require pharmacies to submit supplier invoices and batch numbers on request; suspicious supply chains are audited and blocked.

question: How does CareLoop ensure helpers follow patient privacy at doorstep?
answer: Helpers receive privacy training, anonymized order details, and are prohibited from discussing medical details publicly; violations are penalized.

question: Does CareLoop support audit logs for every prescription order?
answer: Yes  every action (upload, edit, acceptance, substitution) is logged with timestamps and user IDs for compliance audits.

question: How does the platform handle regulated medication quotas (limit per patient)?
answer: System enforces quota rules for controlled substances and alerts pharmacists if orders exceed legal limits; manual doctor verification may be required.

question: What controls exist to prevent helpers from accessing full patient addresses?
answer: Helpers receive shortened or masked address details and access the full location only when they accept the task to minimize unnecessary exposure.

question: How do you handle cross-border pharmaceutical regulations if expanding internationally?
answer: We adapt to local laws by localizing partner onboarding, licensing checks, and data residency to comply with each countrys regulations.

question: Does the app provide consent request flows for sharing medical data with third parties?
answer: Yes  explicit consent flows are presented before sharing data with third parties; users can revoke consent anytime.

question: How is pharmacist identity verified before they approve a prescription?
answer: Pharmacists complete KYC with license verification; approval actions are tied to verified pharmacist profiles for legal accountability.

question: How are recalls handled if a batch is found defective after delivery?
answer: We notify affected customers, coordinate returns with pharmacies or helpers, and facilitate refunds or replacements per regulatory guidance.

question: Does CareLoop enforce carbon copy audit emailing for high-risk prescriptions?

question: Can I reject AI-suggested substitutes?
variations: I dont want a substitute  is that possible?
answer: Yes  you can accept or decline any AI-suggested substitute. If you decline, the system will try other nearby pharmacies or notify you if the original brand is back in stock.

question: Are AI substitution suggestions reviewed by a pharmacist?
answer: Recommended substitutes are flagged in the order and require pharmacist confirmation before dispatch. The pharmacist verifies clinical appropriateness and updates the order if needed.

question: How secure is my prescription data?
variations: How do you protect prescription images?
answer: Prescriptions and health data are encrypted in transit and at rest. Access is restricted to necessary staff, pharmacies, and authorized doctors; data handling follows applicable privacy laws and our security policies.

question: What happens if OCR reads a wrong medicine name?
variations: OCR made a mistake  what then?
How do you fix OCR errors?
answer: If OCR output looks incorrect, either you or the accepting pharmacist can edit the parsed fields before confirmation. The app logs changes and requires pharmacist sign-off for corrected prescriptions.

question: Can the AI detect dangerous drug interactions from my prescription?
variations: Will the system warn about interactions?
Does it check for drug conflicts?
answer: Yes  our backend checks prescriptions against an interaction database and flags potential drug interactions or contraindications. If a risk is detected, the system notifies the pharmacist and suggests a doctor consult before fulfillment.

question: How do I upload a prescription for validation?
variations: How to send my prescription photo?
Where do I add my doctors note?
answer: Tap the chat attach icon, choose Upload Prescription, take a clear photo or select from gallery, and submit. The AI will analyze it and show a parsed summary for your confirmation before sending to pharmacies.

question: Can the OCR detect non-medicine instructions like take with food?
answer: Yes  OCR combined with NLP attempts to extract administration instructions (e.g., take after meals) and flags them for pharmacist confirmation when recognized.

question: How do you handle prescriptions that list meters or device-specific doses (e.g., inhaler puffs)?
answer: The parser recognizes common dose units (puffs, drops, IU) and includes them in parsed fields; ambiguous cases are highlighted for manual verification.

question: Does the system identify allergies mentioned on prescriptions?
answer: If an allergy is written on the prescription or user profile contains allergy data, the system cross-checks and warns pharmacists about potential conflicts.

question: How fast is prescription validation after I upload a photo?
answer: Most uploads are parsed within seconds; full validation including pharmacist review may take longer depending on workload but typically completes within minutes.

question: Will the app suggest pediatric dosing adjustments if age is provided?
answer: When user age or child profile is provided, the AI flags age-sensitive dosing and requests pharmacist or doctor confirmation before fulfillment.

question: Can the OCR identify handwritten dates and doctor signatures?
answer: OCR may detect printed dates and signatures but for legal verification human review is used to confirm authenticity when required.

question: Does the NLP normalize different drug name spellings or abbreviations?
answer: Yes  the NLP normalizes common abbreviations and variant spellings to canonical drug names to improve matching with inventory records.

question: Can I manually correct parsed prescription fields before placing an order?
answer: Yes  after parsing, you see parsed fields and can edit any incorrect entries before sending the order to pharmacies.

question: Are OCR and parsed results kept in my medical history for future reuse?
answer: Parsed prescriptions are saved in your Health Records (with consent) so you can reorder or share them later.

question: How does the system handle combination medications (two active ingredients in one tablet)?
answer: The NLP recognizes combination formulations and maps them to the correct product entries; pharmacists confirm equivalence before dispatch.

question: How do pharmacies join CareLoop?
answer: Pharmacies can sign up via the app or web portal, complete KYC and business verification, upload licenses, and attend a quick onboarding session. Once approved, they start receiving local order broadcasts.

question: How are helper delivery partners registered?
answer: Helpers register through the CareLoop helper app, provide ID and phone verification, complete background checks, and complete basic training. After approval, they become visible for local pickup assignments.

question: How does the helper matching algorithm work?
answer: When a pharmacy hands a ready order to the platform, nearby available helpers receive the pickup request. The system matches by proximity, helper rating, and current load; the first helper to accept picks up the order.

question: How do pharmacies manage inventory in the app?
answer: Pharmacies can add and update stock through their dashboard or POS integration. They can mark availability, set prices, and enable auto-reorder alerts for low-stock items.

question: What are helper safety protocols for pickups?
variations: How do you keep helpers safe?
answer: Helpers undergo basic safety training, are given safety guidelines, and have in-app emergency support. The app shares anonymized delivery details and enforces contactless pickup options when needed.

question: How do pharmacies get paid for orders?
answer: Payments are collected via the app (card, UPI, wallets) and settled to pharmacies on a regular payout schedule (daily/weekly) after deducting commissions and any fees as per the partnership agreement.

question: How are helper earnings calculated?
answer: Helper earnings come from delivery fees and any tips. The app shows a clear fee breakdown per trip; helpers receive payouts on a scheduled basis with a detailed earnings statement.

question: Can a pharmacy prioritize accepted orders?
answer: Yes  pharmacies may enroll in a subscription or priority program that increases visibility to nearby user requests or guarantees priority placement in the order broadcast queue.

question: What if a helper cancels after accepting a pickup?
answer: If a helper cancels after acceptance, the order is re-broadcast to other available helpers; the system logs cancellations, and repeated cancellations affect helper reliability scores.

question: How do we ensure quality across small pharmacies?
answer: CareLoop enforces onboarding checks (licenses, KYC), continuous ratings from users, periodic audits, and optional training/quality programs for pharmacies to keep standards consistent.

question: How can pharmacies set blackout hours when they cant accept orders?
answer: Pharmacies can configure opening hours and blackout periods in their dashboard; during those times they will not receive new order broadcasts.

question: Can helpers indicate whether they have a bike or car for larger deliveries?
answer: Helpers set vehicle type in their profile; matching can prioritize helpers with suitable transport for large or heavy orders.

question: How do micro-pharmacies without POS integrate inventory with CareLoop?
answer: Small stores can use the web dashboard for manual inventory updates or a lightweight CSV upload; POS integrations are optional for larger chains.

question: What performance metrics do pharmacies see to improve service?
answer: Pharmacies see acceptance rate, average preparation time, customer ratings, cancellation reasons, and delivery success rate to help optimize operations.

question: Are there multi-shop bundles for nearby pharmacies to fulfill large orders collaboratively?
answer: In rare cases, the system can split large orders among nearby partner pharmacies if items are spread across stores; the app consolidates billing and delivery.

question: Can helpers set their availability windows each day?
answer: Helpers can toggle availability and set preferred working windows so they only receive assignments during those times.

question: How can a pharmacy escalate a disputed delivery to support?
answer: Pharmacies can file a support ticket from the dashboard including order ID, photos, and notes; support reviews and responds per SLA.

question: Do helper profiles include verification badges for ID and background checks?
answer: Verified helpers display badges indicating completed ID checks and training. Users and pharmacies can filter by verified status.

question: How do pharmacies manage special price lists for institutional buyers?
answer: Pharmacies can assign customer groups and custom price lists in their dashboard to handle institutional or bulk clients separately.

question: Can helpers receive advance payment or retainers for prioritized shifts?
answer: Some local programs allow managed advance payouts or retainers for top-performing helpers; details are handled by local ops and payroll systems.

question: What can the AI Health Assistant help me with?
variations: What does the AI assistant do?
How can the chatbot help me?
answer: The AI Health Assistant helps with symptom guidance, wellness tips, prescription explanations, dosage reminders, product suggestions, and routing you to a doctor or pharmacy when needed.

question: Can I ask the assistant general health questions?
variations: Does the bot answer wellness questions?
Can I get advice on daily health?
answer: Yes  you can ask about skincare, sleep routines, diet, mild symptoms, supplement guides, and everyday wellness. The assistant provides verified suggestions and directs you to a doctor for serious conditions.

question: Does the AI replace a doctor?
answer: No. The AI provides guidance, not medical diagnosis. For clinical decisions, prescriptions, or complex symptoms, the app connects you to a certified doctor.

question: Can the AI help identify my symptoms?
variations: Does the bot check my symptoms?
answer: Yes  the AI asks follow-up questions to understand your symptoms and offers possible explanations with recommended next steps. For anything risky, it directs you to a doctor immediately.

question: Will the AI recommend products?
variations: Can I get skin or wellness product suggestions?
answer: Yes. Based on your concerns, the AI suggests dermatologist-approved or pharmacist-verified products that are available from local partner stores.

question: Can AI remind me to take medicines?
variations: Does the app notify me to take my pills?
answer: Yes. You can set reminders for dosage times, refill dates, recurring prescriptions, and upcoming check-ups. The reminders sync with your calendar if enabled.

question: Does the assistant store my health preferences?
answer: Yes  with your consent, the AI learns your preferences such as allergies, recurring conditions, preferred products, and pharmacies to personalize your health journey.

question: Can AI help interpret my health reports?
variations: Can it explain my blood test?
How does the app interpret lab values?
answer: The AI highlights abnormal values in your lab reports, explains what they typically indicate, and recommends whether a doctor consultation is advisable.

question: Is my conversation with the AI private?
answer: Yes. All AI interactions are end-to-end encrypted and stored securely. Only you can view your chat unless you voluntarily share data with a doctor.

question: Can AI help with fitness or lifestyle planning?
answer: Yes  the AI provides personalized fitness routines, sleep hygiene tips, hydration goals, diet suggestions, and habit-building challenges.

question: Can the AI suggest meal plans based on my dietary restrictions?
answer: Yes  provide your restrictions (e.g., vegetarian, gluten-free, allergies) and the AI will propose meal ideas and shopping suggestions from local stores.

question: Does the AI provide mental wellness micro-tasks (e.g., breathing exercises)?
answer: The AI offers short guided micro-tasks such as breathing exercises, brief mindfulness sessions, and mood tracking prompts.

question: Can the assistant identify patterns from my symptom logs over time?
answer: Yes  with continuous logging the AI detects trends and can summarize recurring symptoms or triggers and recommend follow-up actions.

question: Will the AI recommend community resources like nearby support groups?
answer: The assistant lists local community resources, support groups, and events from the community feed relevant to your condition or interests.

question: Can the AI generate weekly wellness summaries for me?
variations: Weekly recap of my health data
answer: Yes  opt-in to receive weekly summaries highlighting activity, medication adherence, and suggested improvements.

question: Can the AI coach me on habit stacking (e.g., link medication to daily routine)?
answer: The AI suggests habit-stacking techniques to attach health behaviors to daily routines, increasing adherence and making them easier to follow.

question: Does the AI support voice-activated wellness checks during the day?
answer: Yes  enable voice checks for quick daily prompts and habit confirmations using the apps speech interface.

question: Can the AI help me set realistic fitness goals based on my history?
answer: The AI analyzes your past activity and suggests achievable short-term goals and progressive milestones tailored to your baseline.

question: Can the assistant provide reminders for non-medical wellness tasks (like stretching breaks)?
answer: Yes  configure non-medical reminders such as stretching, posture breaks, or eye rest intervals and receive timely alerts.

question: Does the AI adapt suggestions if I report side effects from a medication?
answer: If you report side effects, the assistant flags the incident, suggests immediate safe steps, and recommends contacting a doctor or pharmacist for review.

question: How do I consult a doctor on CareLoop?
variations: See a doctor in the app
answer: You can start a text, audio, or video consultation directly from the app. Choose your specialty, select a doctor, and join the session instantly or schedule one.

question: Are the doctors on CareLoop qualified?
answer: All doctors undergo KYC, license verification, and background checks. Only certified and registered medical professionals can consult through the platform.

question: Can the doctor give me a prescription?
answer: Yes. After your consultation, the doctor can issue a digital prescription which automatically appears in your app for ordering medicines.

question: Can I talk to a doctor instantly?
answer: Yes  the app supports instant consultations depending on doctor availability. You can also request a callback for urgent but non-emergency situations.

question: How much does an online consultation cost?
variations: How much for a telemedicine call?
answer: Fees depend on the doctors specialty and experience. Prices are shown transparently before booking, and you can pay using UPI, cards, or wallets.

question: Can I share previous prescriptions or reports with the doctor?
answer: Yes  you can securely share prescriptions, photos, and lab reports during the consultation. Doctors only see the files you choose to share.

question: Does CareLoop offer follow-up consultations?
answer: Yes. Many doctors offer discounted or free follow-ups within a certain period. Your previous chat history and prescriptions remain visible for continuity.

question: Can I consult a specialist?
answer: Yes  CareLoop offers specialists across dermatology, general medicine, pediatrics, gynecology, mental health, orthopedics, and more.

question: Is telemedicine safe for serious symptoms?
variations: Can I consult online for severe issues?
answer: Telemedicine is ideal for mild to moderate symptoms. For emergencies like chest pain, severe bleeding, or breathing difficulty, seek immediate in-person medical care.

question: What happens if my call with the doctor drops?
answer: If your call disconnects, you can rejoin within the session window. If the issue persists, the system allows rescheduling or refunding based on the situation.

question: Can I request a home visit from local doctors through the app?
answer: Where supported, you can request a home visit. Availability depends on local partner clinics and doctor schedules.

question: Can I record consultations and save them for future reference?
answer: Recording requires consent. If the doctor agrees, sessions can be recorded and saved securely to your health records.

question: How do I book a consultation with a doctor who speaks my language?
variations: Book doctor who speaks local language
answer: Filter doctors by language preference when booking to find clinicians fluent in the language you prefer.

question: Can doctors add follow-up orders (e.g., physiotherapy referrals) directly in the app?
answer: Yes  doctors can add referrals and orders for allied services which appear in your care plan and can be booked through the platform.

question: Are second opinions available through CareLoop?
answer: You can request a second opinion and share the original report or consultation notes with the new clinician for review.

question: Can I schedule multiple patients in my family with one consultation slot (e.g., family consult)?
answer: Group or family consultations are supported with select clinicians; choose a multi-patient booking if the doctor offers it.

question: Does the app let me message the doctor after the consultation for clarifications?
answer: Many doctors allow brief follow-up messages within a defined period; check the doctors follow-up policy before booking.

question: Can I get prescriptions translated into local language instructions?
answer: The app can display prescriptions and dosing instructions in supported local languages for better patient understanding.

question: How is doctor identity verified before a consultation?
answer: Doctors undergo license verification, ID checks, and credential validation before offering consultations on the platform.

question: Can I book a doctor for chronic disease management plans?
answer: Yes  you can enroll in chronic care programs with recurring consultations, care plans, and remote monitoring options where available.

question: How do I book a lab test on CareLoop?
variations: How to schedule a blood test?
How do I request lab tests?
answer: You can book any lab test directly through chat. Select a test, choose a partner lab, schedule a pickup time, and a certified technician or helper will come for sample collection.

question: Who collects my sample for tests?
variations: Who will take my blood sample?
answer: For most tests, a trained phlebotomist from the partner lab collects your sample. In some cases, a verified helper assists with logistics while the phlebotomist handles the actual sampling.

question: Can I choose the lab for my test?
variations: Can I pick my preferred lab?
answer: Yes  you can select from multiple partnered labs based on pricing, distance, rating, or availability.

question: How soon will I get my lab test reports?
answer: Report times vary by test. Most routine tests take 624 hours, while specialized tests may take longer. All reports appear digitally inside your CareLoop account.

question: Can the AI interpret my test results?
answer: Yes. The AI highlights abnormal values, explains general meanings, and suggests whether a doctor consultation is advisable. It does not replace medical diagnosis.

question: What happens if my scheduled test is delayed?
answer: If a delay occurs, youll receive updates via the app. You can reschedule or request a different technician if needed.

question: Is home sample collection safe and hygienic?
answer: Yes  partner labs follow strict hygiene protocols. Technicians use sterilized tools, gloves, and single-use equipment for each patient.

question: Do you offer full body checkups?
answer: Yes  you can book comprehensive health packages including CBC, thyroid, sugar, liver, kidney, vitamin tests, and more through partnered labs.

question: Can I cancel a lab test after booking?
answer: Yes  you can cancel before sample collection. Refunds depend on the labs cancellation policy and appear in your CareLoop wallet or original payment method.

question: Will the doctor review my test results?
variations: How to show reports to doctor?
answer: You can request a doctor consultation after receiving your report. The doctor can view your digital report and provide medical interpretation.

question: Can I request home collection for a fasting blood test and be reminded to fast?
answer: Yes  select fasting required when booking; the app sends fasting reminders and schedules morning pickups as appropriate.

question: Can I compare prices for the same test across partner labs?
answer: Yes  the booking flow shows partner labs with price, turnaround time, and ratings so you can choose the best option.

question: Can labs provide home-based ECG or mobile imaging services?
answer: Some partner labs and vendors offer mobile ECG and imaging; availability depends on location and lab capabilities.

question: Can I add doctor notes when booking a test for specialized processing?
answer: Yes  attach clinician notes or special processing requests during booking; labs review them before sample collection.

question: Can I request expedited lab processing for urgent cases?
answer: If the lab supports expedited processing, you can request it for an additional fee; this option is visible at booking.

question: Can I download lab certificates or official PDF reports for insurance claims?
answer: Yes  official signed PDF reports suitable for insurance claims are available for download after processing.

question: Can labs send me pre-test instructions tailored to my selected tests?
answer: Yes  the app provides tailored pre-test instructions (fasting, medication pauses) immediately after booking.

question: Can I invoice multiple tests together as a health package and get a bundled discount?
answer: Yes  many labs offer bundled packages with discounted pricing that you can select instead of individual tests.

question: Do lab technicians carry identification during home visits?
answer: Yes  technicians carry official ID and the app shows the technicians name and verification badge before arrival.

question: Can I add insurance details to my test booking to claim later?
answer: Yes  add insurer policy details during booking; labs include this information on the invoice to help with claims.

question: What payment methods are supported?
answer: CareLoop supports UPI, credit/debit cards, net banking, and in some regions, cash on delivery. Digital payments are recommended for faster processing.

question: Do I have to pay a convenience fee?
answer: A small convenience fee may apply depending on your location and order type. This fee helps maintain fast delivery and app services.

question: How do I get an invoice for my medicine order?
answer: Invoices are automatically generated by the pharmacy and available in your order details. You can download or print them anytime.

question: What if my payment fails?
answer: If a payment fails, you wont be charged. You can try again with another payment method. For incorrect deductions, refunds are processed within 35 business days.

question: Can I pay after delivery?
answer: Cash on delivery is available in selected areas. However, online payments help pharmacies process your order faster.

question: How do pharmacy payouts work?
answer: Pharmacies receive automated payouts on a daily or weekly schedule. Fees and commissions are deducted transparently, and detailed payout reports are available in the dashboard.

question: How do helpers get paid?
answer: Helpers earn delivery fees and tips. Earnings are transferred to their bank account or wallet based on the payout cycle.

question: Are refunds processed automatically?
answer: Yes  refunds are initiated automatically for cancellations or payment failures. Refunds typically take 37 business days based on your payment method.

question: Can I use a wallet balance to pay?
answer: Yes  if your region supports CareLoop Wallet, you can use your balance to pay for medicines, tests, and consultations.

question: Will I get a separate invoice for delivery charges?
answer: Delivery charges appear as a separate line item on your invoice. You can download a full or itemized bill from your order details.

question: Can I apply promo codes to scheduled or recurring orders?
answer: Yes  promo codes valid for recurring or scheduled orders can be applied during setup if the codes rules allow it.

question: Can I split payment between wallet and card?
answer: Yes  you may use wallet balance first and pay the balance with a card or UPI where supported.

question: Are digital receipts emailed automatically after purchase?
answer: Yes  invoices are sent via email and stored in your order history for download anytime.

question: Can I set a billing address different from my delivery address?
answer: Yes  enter a separate billing address in payment details to be used on invoices.

question: How do taxes (GST/VAT) appear on my invoice?
answer: Invoices show itemized taxes (GST/VAT) per product with totals; GST numbers are available on pharmacy invoices where applicable.

question: Can I schedule automatic wallet top-ups for quick checkout?
answer: Yes  enable auto top-up and set thresholds; the wallet will recharge when balance falls below the set amount.

question: What is the dispute process for a charged but undelivered order?
answer: Open the order and tap Dispute charge  support investigates, and provisional refunds may be offered while we resolve the issue.

question: Can I add multiple cards and set a default payment method?
answer: Yes  add several cards in payment settings and set one as default for faster checkouts.

question: Are transaction histories downloadable for accounting?
answer: Yes  you can export transaction histories as CSV or PDFs from the account dashboard for accounting purposes.

question: Can pharmacies apply custom discounts per invoice at the time of billing?
answer: Yes  pharmacies can add line-item discounts at billing; changes reflect on the invoice and in your order summary.

question: How do I create an account on CareLoop?
answer: You can sign up using your phone number or email. After OTP verification, your profile is created and you can start ordering medicines or using health services instantly.

question: Can I add family members to my account?
answer: Yes  you can create separate profiles for family members to manage their prescriptions, reminders, consultations, and reports.

question: Where can I see my health history?
answer: Your health history, including prescriptions, lab reports, consultations, and past orders, is available in the Health Records section of your profile.

question: Is my health data safe?
answer: Yes  all health data is encrypted and complies with applicable privacy regulations. Only you control who can view or share your medical information.

question: Can I delete my account?
answer: Yes  you can request account deletion from the app settings. Your data will be securely erased as per our retention policies.

question: Can I update my address or contact details?
answer: Yes  you can update your address, contact details, and emergency contacts from the profile settings anytime.

question: How do I upload previous prescriptions to my account?
answer: You can upload prescriptions and medical documents in the Health Records section. The AI will categorize them automatically.

question: Does CareLoop support multiple delivery addresses?
variations: Can I save more than one address?
answer: Yes  you can add multiple delivery addresses, such as home, office, or family homes, and choose one during checkout.

question: Can I share my health data with a doctor?
answer: Yes  you can selectively share prescriptions, test results, and symptoms with your doctor during or before a consultation.

question: What happens if I change my phone number?
answer: You can update your phone number from the profile settings. Verification is done via OTP, and all your health data is preserved.

question: How can I set emergency contacts and quick-call options?
answer: In profile settings add emergency contacts; the app provides a one-tap call option and can share your location with selected contacts during emergencies.

question: Can I enable parental controls for child profiles?
answer: Yes  enable parental controls to restrict purchases, require parental OTP for orders, and manage health information for child profiles.

question: Can I export my familys consolidated health records?
variations: Get single file for family history
answer: Yes  you can export consolidated health records for family members into a single file for backup or transfer to another provider.

question: Can I lock my account remotely if I lose my phone?
answer: Yes  contact support immediately or use the web portal to lock the account temporarily until you recover access.

question: Can I add allergy and intolerance tags to my profile?
answer: Yes  add allergies, intolerances, and drug sensitivities to your profile; the AI and pharmacies use these to prevent unsafe recommendations.

question: How do I enable two-factor authentication (2FA)?
answer: Enable 2FA in security settings using SMS OTP or authenticator apps to add an extra layer of protection to your account.

question: Can I link my wearable accounts to my profile for continuous sync?
answer: Yes  connect supported wearable or health apps in integrations to sync activity, heart rate, and other metrics automatically.

question: Can I request data portability to move my information to another service?
answer: Yes  request a data export in account settings; we provide your records in a standard format for portability.

question: Can I set up role-based access for caregivers and family members?
answer: Yes  grant role-based permissions (viewer, editor, caregiver) to family members to control access to records and actions.

question: How can I enable reduced-visibility mode for sensitive health items?
answer: Use Private Mode to hide specified records from quick views; these items require an extra authentication step to access.

question: What should I do if the app is not working?
answer: Try restarting the app, checking your internet connection, or updating to the latest version. If the issue persists, contact support via the Help section.

question: My order is stuck. What should I do?
answer: Check your order status for updates. If it remains stuck, contact support or use the Report Issue button in your order details.

question: The pharmacy is not responding to my messages. What now?
answer: If a pharmacy does not respond, you can switch to another store or escalate the issue. The system will reassign your request if needed.

question: How do I report a wrong medicine delivered?
answer: Go to your order details and tap Report Wrong Item. Upload a photo of the product, and support will help replace or refund it.

question: My AI assistant answers seem incorrect. What can I do?
answer: You can tap Improve Answer or Report Issue to let us know. For medical uncertainty, please consult a doctor for verified guidance.

question: My payment went through but the order did not confirm. What now?
answer: If payment succeeds but the order fails, the amount is automatically refunded within 37 business days. You can reorder once confirmed.

question: Why am I not receiving notifications?
answer: Ensure notifications are enabled in both your phone settings and the app. Also check if youve accidentally muted reminders.

question: The AI didnt read my prescription correctly. What do I do?
answer: You can manually edit the scanned details or request pharmacist correction before the order is processed. If the error repeats, upload a clearer photo.

question: How do I contact customer support?
answer: You can reach support through in-app chat, email, or the helpline number depending on your region. Help is available 24/7 in most areas.

question: What should I do if my app keeps crashing?
answer: Try clearing cache, updating the app, or restarting your device. If the issue persists, send a debug report through the Help section.

question: Can I create conditional reminders (e.g., remind only if blood sugar > X)?
answer: Yes  if you share supported device metrics, you can set conditional reminders triggered by thresholds (e.g., glucose or BP readings).

question: Can reminders be sent to my caregiver instead of me?
answer: Yes  delegate reminder notifications to authorized caregivers from reminder settings for added support.

question: Can the app suggest habit-stacking sequences to build new health routines?
answer: Yes  the AI suggests habit-stacking strategies (pairing new habits with existing ones) to improve adoption rates.

question: Can I export my wellness progress to share with my doctor?
answer: Yes  export progress reports (activity, adherence, challenges) as PDFs to share during consultations.

question: Do you offer guided mindfulness or breathing exercises?
answer: Yes  short guided exercises are available inside the wellness section to reduce stress and support mental well-being.

question: Can I auto-adjust reminders for travel and time zone changes?
answer: Yes  enable timezone sync so reminders shift automatically when you travel to new time zones.

question: Can I link reminders to a calendar (Google/Outlook)?
answer: Yes  link your calendar to export reminder events so doses and appointments appear alongside your schedule.

question: Can the app suggest micro-habits based on my day length and schedule?
answer: Yes  the AI considers your typical day length and suggests small, actionable habits that fit into your routine.

question: Can I set voice reminders that speak out my medication name?
answer: Yes  enable audio reminders so your device speaks the medication name and dose at scheduled times.

question: Does the app support accessibility features for reminders (e.g., large text, vibrations)?
answer: Yes  accessibility settings allow larger text, stronger vibrations, and high-contrast modes for reminder visibility.
